snippet.textDisplay:
1) A fast rematch does not make sense. If Deontay loses, he will have two losses. If he wins, we have both Tyson and Deontay 1:1, and a draw. So we need another bout. It would be MUCH better for Deontay to fix his technical weaknesses, use a better strategy too - and then simply fight the winner between Tyson and AJ. That would be MUCH better, and everyone wants to see Tyson versus AJ next.

2) Now ... AJ versus Deontay never happened ... and both are guilty of that, making stupid demands. So Eddie Hearn stating it will happen - uhm, sorry, after you did so much hot air, people are NOT going to believe it UNTIL IT REALLY HAPPENS AND NONE OF THEM PULLS OUT.

David Haye had a real injury (cut brow) and pulled out against Tyson Fury. That match never happened.

So, sorry but ... these promotion people such as Eddie talk big but are not always able to keep their promise. So them stating that it WILL happen means ABSOLUTELY NOTHING.
